<h1 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-=F0=9F=93=8CConstructors,Destructo=
rs,CopyConstructors.1">=F0=9F=93=8C Constructors, Destructors, Copy Constru=
ctors</h1>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-1=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3Constructors.1"=
>1=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 <strong>Constructors</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>A <strong>special member function</strong> that is automatically called =
when an <strong>object is created</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Used to <strong>initialize the object</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Name is <strong>same as the class</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>No return type, not even <code>void</code>.</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Types of Constructors:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Default Constructor</strong> =E2=86=92 no parameters</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Parameterized Constructor</strong> =E2=86=92 with parameters</p>=
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Copy Constructor</strong> =E2=86=92 explained later</p></li>
</ol>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example (C++):</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;iostream&gt;
using namespace std;

class Student {
public:
    string name;
    int age;

    // Default Constructor
    Student() {
        name =3D "Unknown";
        age =3D 0;
        cout &lt;&lt; "Default Constructor called" &lt;&lt; endl;
    }

    // Parameterized Constructor
    Student(string n, int a) {
        name =3D n;
        age =3D a;
        cout &lt;&lt; "Parameterized Constructor called" &lt;&lt; endl;
    }

    void display() {
        cout &lt;&lt; "Name: " &lt;&lt; name &lt;&lt; ", Age: " &lt;&lt; ag=
e &lt;&lt; endl;
    }
};

int main() {
    Student s1;             // Default constructor
    Student s2("Alice", 20); // Parameterized constructor

    s1.display();
    s2.display();
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-2=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3Destructors.1">=
2=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 <strong>Destructors</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>A <strong>special member function</strong> automatically called when an =
<strong>object is destroyed</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Used to <strong>release resources</strong> (memory, file handles, etc.)<=
/p></li>
<li>
<p>Name is <strong>same as class</strong>, preceded by <code>~</code>.</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p><strong>No parameters, no return type</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example (C++):</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">class S=
tudent {
public:
    Student() { cout &lt;&lt; "Constructor called" &lt;&lt; endl; }
    ~Student() { cout &lt;&lt; "Destructor called" &lt;&lt; endl; }
};

int main() {
    Student s1;  // Constructor called
}               // Destructor called automatically at end of scope
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-3=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3CopyConstructor=
s.1">3=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 <strong>Copy Constructors</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>A <strong>special constructor</strong> that initializes a new object as =
a <strong>copy of an existing object</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Automatically called when:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>An object is passed by value</p></li>
<li>
<p>An object is returned by value</p></li>
<li>
<p>A new object is initialized from another object</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example (C++):</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;iostream&gt;
using namespace std;

class Student {
public:
    string name;
    int age;

    // Parameterized Constructor
    Student(string n, int a) {
        name =3D n;
        age =3D a;
        cout &lt;&lt; "Parameterized Constructor called" &lt;&lt; endl;
    }

    // Copy Constructor
    Student(const Student &amp;s) {
        name =3D s.name;
        age =3D s.age;
        cout &lt;&lt; "Copy Constructor called" &lt;&lt; endl;
    }

    void display() {
        cout &lt;&lt; "Name: " &lt;&lt; name &lt;&lt; ", Age: " &lt;&lt; ag=
e &lt;&lt; endl;
    }
};

int main() {
    Student s1("Alice", 20);
    Student s2 =3D s1; // Copy constructor called
    s2.display();
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
