clearly with <strong>Single and Multiple Inheritance</strong>.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-=F0=9F=93=8CInheritanceinOOP">=F0=
=9F=93=8C <strong>Inheritance in OOP</strong></h1>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Inheritance is an OOP concept where a <strong>class (child/subclass) acq=
uires properties and behavior</strong> from another <strong>class (parent/s=
uperclass)</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Helps in <strong>code reusability</strong> and <strong>hierarchical mode=
ling</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Key Points:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Parent class</strong> =E2=86=92 Base class / Superclass</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Child class</strong> =E2=86=92 Derived class / Subclass</p></li>
<li>
<p>Child inherits <strong>attributes and methods</strong> of parent.</p></l=
i>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-1=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3SingleInheritan=
ce">1=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 <strong>Single Inheritance</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>A <strong>child class inherits from only one parent class</strong>.</p><=
/li>
</ul>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example (C++):</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;iostream&gt;
using namespace std;

// Parent class
class Vehicle {
public:
    void start() {
        cout &lt;&lt; "Vehicle started" &lt;&lt; endl;
    }
};

// Child class
class Car : public Vehicle {
public:
    void honk() {
        cout &lt;&lt; "Car honks" &lt;&lt; endl;
    }
};

int main() {
    Car c;
    c.start();  // inherited from Vehicle
    c.honk();   // own method
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Key Point:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Child class <code>Car</code> <strong>inherits </strong><code>start()</co=
de> method from <code>Vehicle</code>.</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Diagram:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Vehicle
   |
   v
  Car
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-2=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3MultipleInherit=
ance">2=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 <strong>Multiple Inheritance</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>A <strong>child class inherits from more than one parent class</strong>.=
</p></li>
<li>
<p>Used when a class needs features from <strong>multiple classes</strong>.=
</p></li>
</ul>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example (C++):</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;iostream&gt;
using namespace std;

// Parent class 1
class Vehicle {
public:
    void start() { cout &lt;&lt; "Vehicle started" &lt;&lt; endl; }
};

// Parent class 2
class Horn {
public:
    void honk() { cout &lt;&lt; "Horn sound" &lt;&lt; endl; }
};

// Child class inherits from both Vehicle and Horn
class Car : public Vehicle, public Horn {
public:
    void show() { cout &lt;&lt; "Car is ready" &lt;&lt; endl; }
};

int main() {
    Car c;
    c.start();  // from Vehicle
    c.honk();   // from Horn
    c.show();   // own method
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Key Points:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>Car</code> inherits from <strong>both </strong><code>Vehicle</code=
><strong> and </strong><code>Horn</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>C++ supports multiple inheritance, but <strong>Java does not</strong> (u=
ses interfaces instead).</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Diagram:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Vehicle=
      Horn
   \          /
    \        /
       Car
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-3=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3QuickComparison=
Table">3=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 <strong>Quick Comparison Table</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"b0=
241f43-ef68-496c-9a00-3414c24301d5" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Feature</p></th>
