<h1 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-=F0=9F=93=8CExceptionsinJava">=F0=
=9F=93=8C <strong>Exceptions in Java</strong></h1>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Exceptions are <strong>runtime errors</strong> that can be <strong>caugh=
t and handled</strong> to prevent program crashes.</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Keywords:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>try</code> =E2=86=92 block of code to monitor for exceptions</p></=
li>
<li>
<p><code>catch</code> =E2=86=92 block to handle exceptions</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>throw</code> =E2=86=92 signal an exception</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>throws</code> =E2=86=92 declares that a method may throw an except=
ion</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>finally</code> =E2=86=92 block executed <strong>always</strong>, u=
sed for cleanup</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-Example:JavaExceptionHandling"><st=
rong>Example: Java Exception Handling</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">public =
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int a =3D 10, b =3D 0;

        try {
            int result =3D a / b; // may throw ArithmeticException
            System.out.println("Result: " + result);
        } catch (ArithmeticException e) {
            System.out.println("Exception caught: " + e.getMessage());
        } finally {
            System.out.println("Finally block executed.");
        }

        System.out.println("Program continues...");
    }
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Key Points:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>try</code> monitors code for errors.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>catch</code> handles specific exceptions.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>finally</code> runs whether or not an exception occurs.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-AdvantagesofExceptionsinJava"><str=
ong>Advantages of Exceptions in Java</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"66=
d2c80b-030c-4d2a-b19f-b189df0600d7" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Advantage</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Explanation</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Clean error handling</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Avoids error codes everywhere</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Separation of concerns</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Keeps normal logic separate from error handling</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Resource management</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>finally</code> ensures cleanup (files, streams, etc.)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Multiple exception types</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Different exceptions can be caught differently</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-=F0=9F=93=8CObject-OrientedI/OinJa=
va">=F0=9F=93=8C <strong>Object-Oriented I/O in Java</strong></h1>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Java uses <strong>classes and objects</strong> for input/output.</p></li=
>
<li>
<p>Part of <a href=3D"http://java.io" data-card-appearance=3D"inline" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">http://java.io</a> and <strong>java.uti=
l</strong> packages.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Streams are objects for <strong>reading and writing data</strong>.</p></=
li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-Example:BasicI/OusingScanner(Conso=
leInput)"><strong>Example: Basic I/O using Scanner (Console Input)</strong>=
</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">import =
java.util.Scanner;

class Student {
    String name;
    int age;

    void input() {
        Scanner sc =3D new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("Enter name: ");
        name =3D sc.nextLine();
        System.out.print("Enter age: ");
        age =3D sc.nextInt();
    }

    void display() {
        System.out.println("Name: " + name + ", Age: " + age);
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student s =3D new Student();
        s.input();
        s.display();
    }
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Key Points:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>Scanner</code> is an <strong>object for input</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>System.out</code> is an <strong>object for output</strong>.</p></l=
i>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-Object-OrientedI/OwithFileStreams"=
><strong>Object-Oriented I/O with File Streams</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">import =
java.io.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        try {
            // Create file writer object
            FileWriter writer =3D new FileWriter("example.txt");
            writer.write("Hello, Java OOP I/O!\n");
            writer.close();

            // Read the file
            FileReader reader =3D new FileReader("example.txt");
            BufferedReader br =3D new BufferedReader(reader);
            String line;
            while((line =3D br.readLine()) !=3D null) {
                System.out.println(line);
            }
            br.close();
        } catch(IOException e) {
            System.out.println("Exception caught: " + e.getMessage());
        }
    }
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Key Points:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Streams</strong> (<code>FileWriter</code>, <code>FileReader</cod=
e>, <code>BufferedReader</code>) are <strong>objects</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Supports <strong>OOP design</strong>, operator overloading is not in Jav=
a but object methods achieve the same.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
