<h1 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-=F0=9F=93=8CTemplatesinC++">=F0=9F=
=93=8C <strong>Templates in C++</strong></h1>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Templates allow you to write <strong>generic code</strong> that works wi=
th <strong>any data type</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Instead of writing the same function/class for <code>int</code>, <code>f=
loat</code>, <code>double</code>, etc., you can use <strong>templates</stro=
ng>.</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Types:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Function Templates</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Class Templates</strong></p></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-1=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3FunctionTemplat=
es">1=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 <strong>Function Templates</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>A <strong>generic function</strong> that works with multiple data types.=
</p></li>
</ul>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;iostream&gt;
using namespace std;

// Function template
template &lt;typename T&gt;
T add(T a, T b) {
    return a + b;
}

int main() {
    cout &lt;&lt; add&lt;int&gt;(5, 10) &lt;&lt; endl;        // works with=
 int
    cout &lt;&lt; add&lt;double&gt;(2.5, 3.5) &lt;&lt; endl;  // works with=
 double
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Key Points:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>template &lt;typename T&gt;</code> declares a generic type <code>T=
</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>T</code> is replaced with the <strong>actual type</strong> during =
compilation.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Can also use <code>template &lt;class T&gt;</code> instead of <code>type=
name</code>.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-=F0=9F=94=B9FunctionTemplatewithMu=
ltipleTypes">=F0=9F=94=B9 Function Template with Multiple Types</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">templat=
e &lt;typename T1, typename T2&gt;
void display(T1 a, T2 b) {
    cout &lt;&lt; a &lt;&lt; " and " &lt;&lt; b &lt;&lt; endl;
}

int main() {
    display&lt;int, double&gt;(10, 3.14);
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-2=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3ClassTemplates"=
>2=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 <strong>Class Templates</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>A <strong>generic class</strong> that can work with <strong>any data typ=
e</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;iostream&gt;
using namespace std;

// Class template
template &lt;typename T&gt;
class Box {
    T content;
public:
    void setContent(T value) {
        content =3D value;
    }
    T getContent() {
        return content;
    }
};

int main() {
    Box&lt;int&gt; intBox;
    intBox.setContent(123);
    cout &lt;&lt; "Int Box: " &lt;&lt; intBox.getContent() &lt;&lt; endl;

    Box&lt;string&gt; strBox;
    strBox.setContent("Hello");
    cout &lt;&lt; "String Box: " &lt;&lt; strBox.getContent() &lt;&lt; endl=
;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Key Points:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>Box&lt;int&gt;</code> =E2=86=92 object for integer</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>Box&lt;string&gt;</code> =E2=86=92 object for string</p></li>
<li>
<p>Same <strong>class template</strong> works for multiple types.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-3=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3AdvantagesofTem=
plates">3=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 <strong>Advantages of Templates</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"b6=
b1f105-34ec-48c6-a4ef-8d2420cccfdc" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Advantage</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Explanation</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Code Reusability</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Same function/class works with multiple types</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Type Safety</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Compiler checks types at compile time</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Maintainability</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Avoids writing multiple versions of functions/classes</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Generic Programming</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Supports <strong>generic algorithms</strong> like STL in C++</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
