<h1 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-=F0=9F=93=8CMulti-threadedProgramm=
inginJava.1">=F0=9F=93=8C <strong>Multi-threaded Programming in Java</stron=
g></h1>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Multi-threading is a <strong>Java feature that allows concurrent executi=
on of two or more threads</strong> (lightweight processes) within a program=
.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Each thread has its <strong>own flow of control</strong>, but shares mem=
ory with other threads of the same process.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Useful for <strong>parallelism</strong>, improving performance and respo=
nsiveness.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-1=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3ThreadBasics.1"=
>1=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 <strong>Thread Basics</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Thread</strong>: a small unit of a process that can run independ=
ently.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Main Thread</strong>: Java program starts with a main thread.</p=
></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Java Thread Class</strong>: <code>java.lang.Thread</code></p></l=
i>
<li>
<p><strong>Runnable Interface</strong>: <code>java.lang.Runnable</code></p>=
</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-2=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3CreatingThreads=
inJava.1">2=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 <strong>Creating Threads in Java</strong></h2=
>
<h3 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-Method1:ExtendingThreadClass.1"><s=
trong>Method 1: Extending Thread Class</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">class M=
yThread extends Thread {
    public void run() { // This code runs in a new thread
        for(int i=3D1; i&lt;=3D5; i++) {
            System.out.println("Thread: " + i);
        }
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        MyThread t1 =3D new MyThread();
        t1.start(); // start() creates a new thread and calls run()
       =20
        for(int i=3D1; i&lt;=3D5; i++) {
            System.out.println("Main: " + i);
        }
    }
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Key Points:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>start()</code> =E2=86=92 starts a new thread</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>run()</code> =E2=86=92 defines the thread=E2=80=99s task</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-Method2:ImplementingRunnableInterf=
ace.1"><strong>Method 2: Implementing Runnable Interface</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">class M=
yRunnable implements Runnable {
    public void run() {
        for(int i=3D1; i&lt;=3D5; i++) {
            System.out.println("Runnable Thread: " + i);
        }
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Thread t =3D new Thread(new MyRunnable());
        t.start(); // starts new thread
    }
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Key Points:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Runnable separates <strong>thread logic from thread control</strong>.</p=
></li>
<li>
<p>Preferred when the class already <strong>extends another class</strong>.=
</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-3=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3ThreadMethodsin=
Java.1">3=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 <strong>Thread Methods in Java</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"f6=
b595cc-7e03-4b21-813f-2dee2ffba5fc" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Method</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>start()</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Starts a new thread and calls <code>run()</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>run()</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Contains the code executed by the thread</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>sleep(ms)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Pauses thread for given milliseconds</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>join()</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Waits for thread to finish before continuing main thread</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>setPriority()</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Sets thread priority (1 to 10)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>getName()</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Returns thread name</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>setName()</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Sets thread name</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>isAlive()</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Checks if thread is running</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-4=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3ThreadSynchroni=
zation.1">4=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 <strong>Thread Synchronization</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Problem</strong>: Multiple threads accessing shared resources ca=
n cause <strong>data inconsistency</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Solution</strong>: Use <strong>synchronized methods/blocks</stro=
ng>.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">class C=
ounter {
    private int count =3D 0;

    public synchronized void increment() { // synchronized method
        count++;
    }

    public int getCount() {
        return count;
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws InterruptedException {
        Counter c =3D new Counter();

        Thread t1 =3D new Thread(() -&gt; {
            for(int i=3D0; i&lt;1000; i++) c.increment();
        });

        Thread t2 =3D new Thread(() -&gt; {
            for(int i=3D0; i&lt;1000; i++) c.increment();
        });

        t1.start();
        t2.start();

        t1.join();
        t2.join();

        System.out.println("Count: " + c.getCount()); // Always 2000
    }
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Key Points:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>synchronized</code> ensures <strong>only one thread accesses the m=
ethod at a time</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-5=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3ThreadStatesinJ=
ava.1">5=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 <strong>Thread States in Java</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"43=
601d90-dbbb-49a2-a959-aaaffa137184" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>State</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>New</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Thread object created but <code>start()</code> not called</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Runnable</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Ready to run, waiting for CPU scheduler</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Running</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Thread is executing</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Waiting</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Thread waits indefinitely until notified</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Timed Waiting</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Waiting for specified time</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Terminated</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Thread finished execution</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ObjectOrientedProgramming(OOP)-6=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3AdvantagesofMul=
ti-threading.1">6=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 <strong>Advantages of Multi-threading</=
strong></h2>
